# ðŸ”’ MOBILE-FIRST ENFORCEMENT RULES

## AUTO-CHECK BEFORE ANY CODE CHANGE

Run these checks before committing:

### 1. Sizing Check
```bash
# Search for violations of minimum sizes
grep -r "h-\[1-9\]" src/  # Heights below h-10 on desktop
grep -r "text-xs" src/    # Text smaller than allowed on mobile
grep -r "min-h-\[1-4\]" src/  # Tap targets below 48px
```

### 2. Pattern Check
```bash
# Ensure mobile-first patterns (mobile size first, desktop size with md:)
# CORRECT: h-14 md:h-10
# WRONG: h-10 max-md:h-14
```

### 3. Interactive Element Check
All buttons, links, and form controls must have:
- Minimum 48px tap target on mobile
- Clear focus states
- Proper ARIA labels

### 4. Viewport Check
Test on:
- 360x800 (Samsung Galaxy S8)
- 375x667 (iPhone SE)
- 390x844 (iPhone 12 Pro)

NO horizontal scroll allowed.

### 5. Typography Check
- Body text: Never below 17px on mobile
- Labels: Never below text-base (16px) on mobile
- Headings: Never below text-lg (18px) on mobile

## VIOLATIONS = REJECTED

Any violation requires:
1. Fix the violation
2. Re-test on mobile viewport
3. Update MOBILE_FIRST_LOCKED.md if adding new patterns
4. Get approval before merging

## PROTECTED FILES

These files have ðŸ”’ LOCKED sections:
- src/index.css
- tailwind.config.ts
- public/manifest.json
- index.html (viewport meta)

Changes to locked sections require mobile testing proof.
